modules.description: Provides functions for string manipulation, list transformations, and basic arithmetic operations. Works with strings, lists, and integers to perform tasks like splitting, filtering, and aggregating data. Used to process log entries, clean input data, and generate summary statistics.

This module offers system-level operations for file manipulation, environment management, and process control, along with diagnostics for runtime configurations and hardware details. It works with file paths, environment variables, signal identifiers, and system metadata, enabling tasks like directory traversal, signal handling, and version checks. Use cases include managing file system interactions, monitoring resource limits, and accessing command-line arguments for runtime customization.
